==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tornado
<hw>Tor*na"do</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Tornadoes</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[From Sp. or Pg.
<ets>tornar</ets> to turn, return, L. <ets>tornare</ets> to turn, hence,
a whirling wind. The Sp. & Pg. <ets>tornada</ets> is a return. See
<er>Turn</er>.]</ety> <def>A violent whirling wind; specifically
<fld>(Meteorol.)</fld>, a tempest distinguished by a rapid whirling and
slow progressive motion, usually accompaned with severe thunder,
lightning, and torrents of rain, and commonly of short duration and
small breadth; a small cyclone<-- twister -->.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tornaria</ent>⟦br⟧
